title: For Sale:  BROWNING MODEL 1910 Taken from ww2 soldier w/Arny Trophy Document, photo, holster etc.
postcontent: This listing is for a 32 caliber browning model 1910. This is the model marked FN for Fabrique Nacional of Belgium.  This gun was fired a a US SOLDIER in Japan during ww2.  It was the last shot every fired by that Japanese soldier, and the GI brought the gun back to the United States as a souvenir. Also included is the paper from his lieutenant, regarding this gun being considered a souvenir. The gun comes with the holster and clip.   There is also a photo of the soldier included as well, standing with his Jeep. This soldier fight on in the Korean War, and we have his Purple Heart is well. Later  he took the recoil spring out of the gun, as he was nervous that his children would fire it at each other. This soldier died a few years ago, and his son could not find the spring. We have a estimate from a gunsmith, that says he can get this back into working order for $115. Overall the gun is in good shape, it is an interesting batch of items from an old soldier.
